  <problem>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of Process Centric Implementation is to succesfully implement a business&amp;nbsp;software solution with&#xD;
    predictable outcomes.&#xD;
&lt;/p></problem>
  <background>Process Centric Implementation was developed over multiple decades of consulting by Tory Bjorklund to fill a void in the&#xD;
marketplace. Tory joined Stoneridge Software in 2013 and led an initiative to adopt this methodology for all implementation&#xD;
projects undertaken by Stoneridge Software.</background>
  <goals>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Process Centric Implementation is driven by the Client Delivery Manifesto (link) that was developed by Stoneridge&#xD;
    Software as a declaration of our intent to create an implementation methodology that would meet the demands of the&#xD;
    marketplace and fill a void to delivery usable business software solution in a predictable manner with outcomes that&#xD;
    meet our client expectations.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The specific goals Process Centric implementation addresses as outlined in the manifesto are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Deliver a solution within the time and budget constraints of the original Statement of Work&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurably enhance the client's ability to conduct their business&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Maintain and support the solution for its entire lifecycle&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></goals>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription>
